Industrial Diagnostics3.1 Pre-Use Inspections and Testing Procedures3.1.1 Material Integrity TestingBefore using the Thirsttrek AquaFlow Pro hydration system, it is imperative to conduct athorough material integrity test to ensure that the reservoir is free from defects that couldcompromise its performance and the safety of the user. The following steps outline theprotocol for the material integrity testing:1.

Visual Inspection: Examine the BPA-free reservoir for any signs of damage, such ascracks, punctures, or discoloration. Pay close attention to the seams and corners, wherestress can cause weaknesses.2. Pressure Test: Utilize a specialized pressure testing apparatus to subject the reservoirto controlled internal pressure. Follow the manufacturer's guidelines for theappropriate pressure levels and duration of the test. Any leaks or ruptures detectedduring this test indicate a failure of material integrity.3.

Ultrasonic Inspection: Employ an ultrasonic thickness gauge to measure the thicknessof the reservoir walls at various points. Any deviations from the expected thicknessmay indicate a defect in the material.Note: These tests should be performed in accordance with the ASTM D3078 standard fordetecting gross leaks in flexible packaging containing a headspace gas.3.1.2 Flow Rate CalibrationTo ensure optimal performance of the AquaFlow Pro's easy-flow bite valve, it is essential toconduct a flow rate calibration before each use.

The following steps outline the procedurefor flow rate calibration:1. Measurement Setup: Use a precision flow meter and tubing of the appropriatediameter and length to create a closed loop system with the AquaFlow Pro reservoirand bite valve.2. Calibration Process: Open the bite valve and allow water to flow through the system ata constant rate. Measure the flow rate using the flow meter and compare it to theexpected flow rate specified in the Thirsttrek AquaFlow Pro technical specifications.

Adjustment: If the measured flow rate deviates from the expected value, adjust thebite valve according to the manufacturer's instructions until the desired flow rate isachieved.Note: The flow rate calibration should be conducted in compliance with the ISO 8537standard for determining the flow rate of a hydraulic fluid power valve.3.2 Post-Use Analysis and Maintenance3.2.

Drying Process: Allow the reservoir to air dry in a clean, well-ventilated area. 2 Strap Tension MeasurementThe adjustable straps of the AquaFlow Pro play a crucial role in ensuring a comfortable andsecure fit for the user. Visual Inspection: Examine the bite valve for any signs of wear, such as cracking,tearing, or deformation. Pay particular attention to the area where it connects to thereservoir tubing.2. Observe for any leaks, irregularities in water flow, ordifficulty in opening and closing the valve.3. Replacement: If the bite valve shows signs of wear or fails the operational test, itshould be replaced with a genuine Thirsttrek replacement part, following themanufacturer's instructions.Note: Bite valve wear assessment should be performed in accordance with the ISO 80000-8standard for quantities and units of water and wastewater engineering.

Regulatory Compliance4.1 BPA-Free Certification StandardsThe AquaFlow Pro hydration system from Thirsttrek meets the BPA-Free certificationstandards as outlined by the US Food and Drug Administration (FDA) and the EuropeanFood Safety Authority (EFSA). The BPA-free reservoir is manufactured using materials thatcomply with the following standards:FDA 21 CFR 177.1580: This regulation specifies the permitted ingredients andconditions of use for olefin polymers, which are used in the fabrication of the reservoir.EFSA 10/2011: The materials used in the AquaFlow Pro reservoir comply with themigration limits set by EFSA for plastic materials and articles intended to come intocontact with food.
